Description: Calcite fragment: this thick curved fragment is incised with parts of the Horus name, prenomen and nomen of Ramses III. It may have come from the side of a basin or altar. Only the upper portion of this piece has been preserved with losses on both sides. The back surface is rough and broken. There are no traces of colour.
Bibliographic references: Bierbrier 1982 / Hieroglyphic texts from Egyptian stelae, etc., in the British Museum, Part 10. (pl.28)
Condition: Fair. Only the upper portion of this piece has been preserved with losses on both sides. The back surface is rough and broken.
Acquisition name: Purchased from: Rev Greville John Chester
